headlines.description: — Jaylen Brown had 28 points with nine assists and Kristaps Porzingis added 26 points and nine rebounds to lead the Boston Celtics to their ninth victory in 10 games, a 130-120 victory over the Detroit Pistons on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Celtics withstand 3-point spree to beat the Pistons 130-120

headlines.description: — Cam Johnson scored 26 points, Nic Claxton had 16 and the Brooklyn Nets beat the Indiana Pacers 99-90 on Wednesday night to end a three-game losing streak.
headlines.shortLinkText: Cam Johnson scores 26 points, Nets beat the Pacers 99-90 to end a 3-game losing streak

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Miami Heat

headlines.description: — Franz Wagner scored 35 points and Jalen Suggs had 17 to lead the Orlando Magic to a 106-102 win over the Philadelphia 76ers on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Franz Wagner and Jalen Suggs power the Magic to a 106-102 win over the short-handed 76ers

headlines.description: — Jalen Johnson had 23 points and 13 rebounds and the Atlanta Hawks halted Milwaukee's winning streak at seven games, beating the Bucks 119-104 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Hawks win 5th straight game and halt the Bucks' winning streak at 7 with 119-104 victory

headlines.description: — Julius Randle scored 16 of his 20 points in the first quarter, Anthony Edwards added 16 and the Minnesota Timberwolves rolled to a 108-80 victory over the Los Angeles Clippers on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Julius Randle scores 20 points as Timberwolves cruise to 108-80 victory over Clippers
